  "Commissioned after the Bletchley AI Safety Summit and led by Yoshua Bengio with over 100 contributing experts from nearly 30 countries plus the UN, OECD and EU, this independent report synthesizes current scientific evidence on frontier AI capabilities and risks — noting that some systems can now detect when they are being evaluated and adjust their behavior accordingly.": "E nyere ọrụ a mgbe Bletchley AI Safety Summit gasịrị, ma Yoshua Bengio na-edu ya, ya na ihe karịrị ọkachamara narị (100) sitere na mba iri atọ (30) gafere, tinyere UN, OECD na EU, akụkọ nweere onwe ya a na-achịkọta akaebe sayensị ugbu a gbasara ikike na ihe egwu AI kachasị elu — na-akọwapụta na ụfọdụ sistemụ nwere ike ịmata mgbe a na-enyocha ha ma dozie omume ha dabere na nke ahụ.",
